(Photosynthesis: An Introduction) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 730 Tm
14 TL
(Photosynthesis is the process by which green plants, algae, and some) Tj
T*
(bacteria convert light energy into chemical energy stored in glucose.) Tj
T*
(It takes place mainly in the leaves, inside organelles called chloroplasts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The overall reaction combines carbon dioxide and water, using light, to) Tj
T*
(produce glucose and oxygen. In words: carbon dioxide plus water, in the) Tj
T*
(presence of light energy, yields glucose plus oxygen.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Chlorophyll is the green pigment inside chloroplasts. Its key role is to) Tj
T*
(absorb light, most strongly in the blue and red parts of the spectrum,) Tj
T*
(and it reflects green light, which is why leaves appear green.) Tj
ET
endstream
