/F1 18 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 760 Tm
(The Two Stages of Photosynthesis) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 730 Tm
14 TL
(Photosynthesis happens in two connected stages.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. The light-dependent reactions occur in the thylakoid membranes.) Tj
T*
(   They capture light energy and use it to split water molecules, a) Tj
T*
(   process called photolysis. This releases oxygen as a by-product and) Tj
T*
(   produces energy carriers known as ATP and NADPH.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. The light-independent reactions, also called the Calvin cycle, occur) Tj
T*
(   in the stroma. They do not need light directly. Instead they use the) Tj
T*
(   ATP and NADPH from the first stage to fix carbon dioxide into glucose.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A common misconception is that the Calvin cycle happens at night. In fact) Tj
T*
(it depends on the products of the light reactions, so it typically runs) Tj
T*
(during the day, just without using light itself.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
