(Why Photosynthesis Matters) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 730 Tm
14 TL
(Photosynthesis is the foundation of most food chains on Earth. Plants are) Tj
T*
(primary producers: they make their own food and become the energy source) Tj
T*
(for the organisms that eat them.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The process also releases the oxygen that most living things need to) Tj
T*
(breathe, and it removes carbon dioxide from the atmosphere, playing an) Tj
T*
(important role in regulating the global carbon cycle.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Several factors affect the rate of photosynthesis, including light) Tj
T*
(intensity, carbon dioxide concentration, and temperature. Increasing a) Tj
T*
(limiting factor speeds up the rate until another factor becomes limiting.) Tj
ET
endstream
